    "The 51.5% of them are argumentative essay type where as the 48.5% of them are explanatory essay type.",
    "The essays are written by elementary, middle and high school students and are graded by three evaluators into 11 rubric sub categories scores.",
    "TOEFL11 4 dataset is a corpus collected by Blanchard et al. (2013).",
    "It was created by sampling from a set of TOEFL essays written between 2006 and 2007 in response to eight prompts by non-native writers.",
    "The dataset contains a total of 12,100 essays, which were graded by two human raters on a 5-point-scale."
